#Approach:

String to Integer (atoi) – Simulation Approach

Is problem me hume string ko integer me convert karna hai,
lekin kuch rules follow karne hote hain jaise spaces, sign, overflow, non-digit characters.

Step 1: Sabse pehle string ke starting ke extra spaces remove karte hain (trim).
Step 2: Check karte hain ki next character '-' hai ya '+'.
Agar '-' hai to sign negative kar dete hain, agar '+' hai to positive hi rehta hai.
Step 3: Ab digits read karna start karte hain.
Har digit ko result = result * 10 + digit se number banate hain.
Step 4: Har step par overflow check karte hain.
Agar number Integer.MAX_VALUE se bada ho jaye to MAX_VALUE return kar dete hain.
Agar Integer.MIN_VALUE se chhota ho jaye to MIN_VALUE return kar dete hain.
Step 5: Jaise hi non-digit character milta hai, reading stop kar dete hain.
Step 6: End me result ko sign se multiply karke return kar dete hain.

Is tarah hum string ko integer me safely convert kar lete hain.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(1)

#Code:

class Solution {
    public int myAtoi(String s) {
        long result = 0;
        int sign = 1;
        int i = 0;

        //remove extra blank spaces
        s = s.trim();
        int n = s.length();
        // Checking if string is empty
        if(n == i){
            return 0;
        }

        //checking for optional + or - sign
        if(s.charAt(i) == '-'){
            sign = -1;
            i++;
        }else if(s.charAt(i) == '+'){
            i++;
        }

        // main logic 
        while(i < n && Character.isDigit(s.charAt(i))){
            int digit = s.charAt(i) - '0';
            result = result*10 + digit;

            if (sign * result > Integer.MAX_VALUE) return Integer.MAX_VALUE;
            if (sign * result < Integer.MIN_VALUE) return Integer.MIN_VALUE;

            i++;
        }
        return (int)(result * sign);
    }
}
